==Starting the event==
===Talking to the Easter Bunny===
* '''Player:''' Hello there, Easter Bunny. Is everything alright?
* '''Easter Bunny:''' Oh my, oh my!
* '''Player:''' What's wrong?
* '''Easter Bunny:''' No, no. This can't be happening!
* '''Player:''' Take a deep breath, calm down. Tell me what's wrong.
* '''Easter Bunny:''' I thought for once everything would run as smooth as milk chocolate.
* '''Easter Bunny:''' I had everything prepared! The eggs, the baskets - I even straightened my ears before I got here.
* '''Player:''' Straightened your ears? How would you even-
* '''Easter Bunny:''' And then disaster struck! I counted my eggs backwards, forwards, upside-down and up, but alas... One is missing.
* '''Player:''' Are you sure you brought the right amount?
* '''Easter Bunny:''' Absolutely! I have an entire year to plan for Easter. What do you think I do when I'm not here celebrating with you?
* '''Player:''' Well, I suppose I never thought about that.
* '''Easter Bunny:''' I'm at home, painting and counting eggs, of course! And tending to my chickens.
* '''Easter Bunny:''' Oh, I can't stomach this. [player name], won't you help me find the missing egg?
* {{tselect|Start the Easter event?}}
* {{topt|Yes.}}
** '''Easter Bunny:''' Thank you! Archibald left a note before he left. It may help you find him. It's on a table just over there.
** '''Easter Bunny:''' He is a curious one. Whenever he hears of interesting places, he tends to want to go there.
** '''Player:''' Archibald? You named the egg?
** '''Easter Bunny:''' Of course. I name all my eggs. There's also Eggward, Eggon, Leggolas and Greggory, to name a few.
** '''Player:''' And you teach them to write, too?
** '''Easter Bunny:''' {{colour|#0000b2|--The Easter Bunny winks at you.--}}
** '''Easter Bunny:''' Go on now, before he travels too far!
** '''Player:''' Guess I'm off to chase an egg.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|No.}}
** '''Player:''' I don't have time at the moment, sorry.
** '''Easter Bunny:''' Oh Archibald, oh Archibald. Wheresoever art thou, Archibald?
** {{tact|end}}

===Searching the note on a table before starting the event===
* '''Player:''' I should probably talk to the Easter Bunny before I take anything.
* {{tact|end}}

===Searching the note on a table after starting the event===
* {{tcond|If the player has no inventory space:}}
** {{tbox|You don't have enough space to pick up the note.}}
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tbox|pic=Scribbled notes detail.png|You pick up the note left by Archibald.}}
* {{tact|end}}

==The hunt for Archibald==
===Talking to the Easter Bunny before reading the notes===
* '''Easter Bunny:''' Did you have a look at the note?
* '''Player:''' Not yet, no.
* '''Easter Bunny:''' It's on a table just over there, you should take it and give it a read.
* '''Player:''' Ok!
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the Easter Bunny after losing the notes===
* '''Player:''' I lost the notes.
* {{tcond|If the player has no inventory space:}}
** '''Easter Bunny:''' Thats{{sic}} okay, I made some copies but you'll need to make some space to be able to take them.
** {{tact|end}}
* '''Easter Bunny:''' Thats{{sic}} okay, I made some copies so here you go.
* {{tact|end}}

===Talking to the Easter Bunny after picking up the first note===
* '''Player:''' Can you help me understand where Archibald is?
* '''Easter Bunny:''' Certainly, let me see what Archibald has left you with...
* {{tcond|If the player has not read the note yet:}}
** '''Easter Bunny:''' You should read the note Archibald left you.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player has already read the note:}}
** '''Easter Bunny:''' It sounds like you must seek out a potion maker. Try in west Varrock.
** {{tact|end}}

